    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1958-03-11T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1958-03-11T12:00:00-05:00" n="30"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d30">
                <head>30. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Cuba</gloss> to the <gloss
                        type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d30fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 737.00/3–1158. Secret; Priority.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Havana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1958-03-11T12:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 11, 1958—noon</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>524. Catholic Church now openly and actively sponsoring same objective as ours—a
                    peaceful solution.</p>
                <p>Papal Nuncio<note n="2" xml:id="d30fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_CML1">Monsignor Luigi Centoz</persName>.</note>
                    informed me eve March 10: <list>
                        <label>(A)</label>
                        <item>If present Harmony Commission is unable to make progress Church may
                            suggest present Commission retire.</item>
                        <label>(B)</label>
                        <item>Then Church may appoint committee of Bishops consisting of Archbishops
                            of Oriente, Matanzas, and Las Villas.</item>
                        <label>(C)</label>
                        <item>
                            <persName corresp="#p_CRF1">Castro</persName>’s life was saved by Perez
                            Serrante, Archbishop of Oriente, some years ago. Church hopes <persName
                                corresp="#p_CRF1">Castro</persName> still has sense of
                            obligation.</item>
                        <label>(D)</label>
                        <item>Archbishop of Oriente will exert full pressure persuade <persName
                                corresp="#p_CRF1">Castro</persName> agree to peaceful
                            solution.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Two factors in situation are disturbing: <list>
                        <label>(1)</label>
                        <item>Efforts of Harmony Commission do not yet have full confidence and
                            support from all principal non-revolutionary groups. We believe
                            Commission should have concentrated on obtaining such support.</item>
                        <label>(2)</label>
                        <item>Influence of 26 July movement appears to have increased alarmingly
                            within recent weeks. This renders more difficult reaching of any
                            understanding with <persName corresp="#p_BZF1"
                            >Batista</persName>.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_CRF1">Castro</persName> rejected peace negotiations
                    through non-political Harmony Commission (<gloss target="#t_EMBTEL1"
                        >Embtel</gloss> 523, March 11<note n="3" xml:id="d30fn3">Not printed.
                        (Department of State, Central Files, 737.00/3–1158)</note>). <persName
                        corresp="#p_CRF1">Castro</persName> repeated demand that <pb facs="0085"
                        n="53" xml:id="pg_53"/>
                    <gloss target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss> allow Cuban newspaperman visit Sierra
                    Maestra doubt [<hi rend="italic">re-doubt</hi>?].</p>
                <p>Present political situation is delicate, difficult and unpredictable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SEET1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
